idCitation.resTitle: 2024 Primary & General Elections Voting Tabulation Districts (VTDs)

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Voting Tabulation Districts (VTDs) are created for the purpose of relating 2020 Census population data to Texas Legislative Council election data. The Voting Tabulation Districts feature class is used in RedAppl, DistrictViewer, and other Texas Legislative Council mapping and reporting applications.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Statewide feature class of 2024 Primary & General Elections Voting Tabulation Districts (VTDs) on 2020 Census geography. VTDs are voting precincts represented using 2020 Census block geography. Some voting precinct boundaries do not use census geography, so the boundary of a VTD may differ from the actual corresponding voting precinct's boundary. The VTDs closely match the 9,657 precincts in effect for the 2024 General Election. On the occasion that a precinct is in two non-contiguous pieces, the VTD is suffixed. For example, if precinct 0001 is two non-contiguous areas, the corresponding VTDs would be VTD 0001A and VTD 0001B. If a voting precinct cannot be represented using census geography, it is consolidated into an adjacent precinct's corresponding VTD. There are 9,712 VTDs in the 2024 General Election VTDs feature class.

Note: The 2024 Primary & General Elections VTDs feature class is not the same as the Voting Districts in the Census Bureau's TIGER/Line Shapefile and do not correspond with the population data reported for the Voting Districts in the Census Bureau's 2020 Census State Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171) Summary File.
